Package: monecascale
Title: Scalable Backends for MONECA Mobility Clustering
Description: Provides scalable clustering backends for the moneca package,
    starting with hierarchical degree-corrected stochastic block model
    (DC-SBM) inference via moneca_sbm(). Designed as a sibling package
    that extends moneca beyond classification-scale mobility matrices
    while reusing moneca's output contract and downstream analysis /
    plotting stack. The load-bearing theoretical observation is that
    moneca's relative-risk matrix RR = O / E is the DC-SBM residual
    under identity block interaction, so SBM inference is a principled
    scalable drop-in for the clique-enumeration step.
